records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody on WRIT.
The State moves to delete all enhancers on count 1.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge in count 1 of deliver Methamphetamine.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in counts 2 and 3.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of five (5) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision, concurrent with the sentences presently being served on 09 CF 48 and 09 CF 296.
The Court finds the defendant eligible for both the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) Pay court costs of $700.34;
2) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) maintain fulltime employment, schooling, work search or combination;
6) provide a DNA sample.
Minutes.
